Patch summary:
Apply the framework and SystemUI desktop contract. This patch gathers the
platform-level behavior that makes the guest act like a desktop VM: desktop-mode
defaults, freeform/window behavior, display power behavior, storage reporting,
keyguard clock suppression, status bar/shade adjustments, Quick Settings
desktop cleanup, and other VM-facing framework defaults.

Most of the changes are about replacing phone assumptions with desktop ones.
The guest has no useful battery saver, flashlight, wallet, auto-rotate, or
screen-sleep affordance, and its display/window model is host-driven. For the
desktop product, the Quick Settings brightness slider is also replaced
functionally with a media-volume slider while reusing the existing slider
placement, and VM-irrelevant QS tiles can be blocklisted by product resources.
Keeping that policy in the framework layer gives Launcher and the product
overlays a stable desktop contract to build on.

Also reduce benign desktop VM framework logspam. Recents cleanup can run before
the per-user recent task/image directories have been created on a fresh userdata
image; create or treat those directories as empty instead of logging repeated
errors.


